  
 Build & run  

From inside the container:

```bash
cd /workspace/ros2_ws
colcon build --packages-select cara_motion_control
source install/setup.bash
ros2 run cara_motion_control head_expression_node
```

If that works, test topic input:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /cara/affect_state std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'happy'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /cara/affect_state std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'sad'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /cara/affect_state std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'neutral'}"
```

---

## 5) If `ros2 run` still canâ€™t see it, do these two quick diagnostics

### A) Confirm the executable is installed

```bash
ls install/cara_motion_control/lib/cara_motion_control/
```

You should see `head_expression_node` in there.

### B) Confirm ROS can list it

```bash
ros2 pkg executables cara_motion_control
```

It should list `cara_motion_control  head_expression_node`.

